text: How does a table help you make sense of the relationship between two variables in a situation?

Possible student answers at this time:

Tables help you to quickly notice differences or changes in the number of jumping jacks for each 10 seconds (rates).

The variables in the relationship are named in the first cells of the table. So you can quickly see what the variables are.

You can see if the relationship is consistent or not by looking at change in the number of jumping jacks for each interval of 10 seconds.
